{{short description|A slow warm water current that flows to the east along the Guinea coast of West Africa}}
{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
[[Image:South_Atlantic_Gyre.png|350px|thumb|right|The South Atlantic Gyre.]]

The '''Guinea Current''' is a slow warm water current that flows to the east along the [[Guinea (region)|Guinea]] coast of [[West Africa]]. It has some similarity to the [[Equatorial Counter Current]] in the Indian and Pacific Oceans.

