{{Infobox islands | name = Ilhéu Gabado | native name = <!-- or local name to remove the "native name:" prefix --> | sobriquet = <!-- or nickname --> | image alt = |pushpin_map =Sao Tome |pushpin_label_position =bottom |pushpin_map_caption =Location off [[São Tomé Island]] | map caption = | location = Southwest of the island of [[São Tomé Island|São Tomé]], [[São Tomé and Príncipe]] | coordinates = {{coord|0.1316|6.480796|type:isle_region:ST|display=inline,title}} | archipelago = | total islands = | major islands = | area km2 = <!-- or area m2 or area ha --> | area footnotes = | rank = | length km = <!-- or length m --> | length footnotes = | width km = <!-- or width m --> | width footnotes = | coastline km = <!-- or coastline m --> | coastline footnotes = | elevation m = | elevation footnotes = | highest mount = <!--name--> | Country heading = | country = [[São Tomé and Príncipe]] | demonym = | population = 0 | population as of = | density km2 = | density footnotes = | ethnic groups = | website = | additional info = }} '''Ilhéu Gabado''' is an uninhabited islet in the [[Gulf of Guinea]] and is one of the smaller islands of [[São Tomé and Príncipe]].<ref>[http://wikimapia.org/#lang=en&lat=0.1316&lon=6.480796&z=18&m=b Ilhéu Gabado]</ref> The islet lies 0.4 km off the southwest coast of the [[São Tomé Island|island of São Tomé]]. Due north is another islet, [[Ilhéu de São Miguel]].
