{{Infobox settlement |name = Leava |other_name = |native_name = |settlement_type = Village |image_skyline = |imagesize = |image_caption = |pushpin_map = Futuna |pushpin_label_position = right |pushpin_map_caption = Location in Futuna Island |pushpin_mapsize = 300 |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = {{flag|France}} |subdivision_type1 = Territory |subdivision_name1 = {{flag|Wallis and Futuna|local}} |subdivision_type2 = Island |subdivision_name2 = [[Futuna (Wallis and Futuna)|Futuna]] |subdivision_type3 = Chiefdom and District |subdivision_name3 = [[Sigave]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |population_as_of = 2008 |population_footnotes = |population_total =480 |population_density_km2 = |timezone = [[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]] |utc_offset = |coordinates = {{coord|14|17|45.96|S|178|9|30.6|W|region:WF|display=inline,title}} |elevation_footnotes = |elevation_m = |elevation_ft = |website = |footnotes = }} '''Leava''' is a village and the administrative centre of the chiefdom of [[Sigave]] on the French Pacific island of [[Futuna Island, Wallis and Futuna|Futuna]], part of the [[Wallis and Futuna]] group.
